# Backend Rules (Go net/http, no framework)

- Keep backend code idiomatic Go and maintain separation across `internal/controllers`, `internal/services`, and `internal/routes`.
- Preserve the existing API surface unless a task explicitly requires contract changes:
  - `POST /api/commits`
  - `POST /api/standup`
  - `GET /api/llm/providers`
  - `POST /api/llm/connect`
  - `POST /api/llm/download`
  - `POST /api/chat`
- Return structured JSON error responses with meaningful HTTP status codes.
- Preserve streaming behavior for `POST /api/llm/download` and `POST /api/chat`.
- Keep runtime configuration env-driven (`PORT`, `OLLAMA_HOST`) and consistent with `docker-compose.yml`.
